{"questionId":"9828","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The Happy Straw Company manufactures drinking straws.</p>\n<p>The straws are packaged in small closed rectangular boxes, each with length 8 cm, width 4 cm&nbsp;and height 3 cm. The information is shown in the diagram.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/2e2c01e0ec88edea5a6fb1b1e3c4e5513ac32546.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Calculate the length AG.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\sqrt {{8^2} + {4^2} + {3^2}} \">\n  <msqrt>\n    <mrow>\n      <msup>\n        <mn>8</mn>\n        <mn>2</mn>\n      </msup>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>+</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <msup>\n        <mn>4</mn>\n        <mn>2</mn>\n      </msup>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>+</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <msup>\n        <mn>3</mn>\n        <mn>2</mn>\n      </msup>\n    </mrow>\n  </msqrt>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">(AG =) 9.43 (cm) (9.4339…,&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\sqrt {89} \">\n  <msqrt>\n    <mn>89</mn>\n  </msqrt>\n</math></span>)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9828","referenceCode":"SPM.2.SL.TZ0.4b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Calculate the length AG.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.3—Differentiating polynomials, n E Z","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.6—Stationary points, local max and min","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.7—Optimisation"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}